  "texts": [
    "To address the lack of reference in the binary classification setup, we adopt a relativistic formulation: the critic takes a triplet (q, a, a *) consisting of one policy answer and one expert answer, and outputs which is better or tie if they are equal in quality.",
    "This resolves the degeneracy where the critic is forced to differentiate even when the policy is optimal.",
    "We empirically show that the tie option is crucial for better performance (see Appendix D.2).",
    "Formally, the relativistic critic c ϕ takes a question q and two candidate answers (a (1), a (2)) and returns a label ℓ ∈ {1, 2, tie}.",
    "Assuming one expert and one policy answer, we can define:"
  ]
}